On the true identity of Schendylurus (Schendylotyn) integer Chamberlin, 1926, a termitophilous ballophilid centipede (Chilopoda: Geophilomorpha)Schendylurus (Schendylotyn) integer Chamberlin, 1926, originally described as a member of the Schendylidae, is transferred here to the Ballophilidae as Taeniolinum integer n. comb. and redescribed after the type specimen. Taeniolinum setosum guadeloupensis Demange and Pereira, 1985 is elevated to specific rank.